Distributed Cache Replication (Leader–Follower Model)

Use Case

Think of systems like Amazon or Netflix where cached data must be replicated across regions for low latency.

Concept

Leader node handles writes
Followers replicate asynchronously
Eventual consistency
Handles read-heavy systems


FAANG-Level Insights
Consistency Model → Eventual consistency (not strong)
Failure Case → What if follower fails? → Retry queue / WAL (Write Ahead Log)
Scaling → Add more followers (read scaling)
Real Tech → Similar to Redis replication
Tradeoff (CAP) → Availability > Consistency

